### 3.2. Vector fields and their derivatives

A vector field above \mathcal{P}\_{2}(\mathbb{R}^{d}) is typically a map V defined on \mathcal{P}\_{2}(\mathbb{R}^{d}) such that V(\mu)\in T\_{\mu}(\mathcal{P}\_{2}(\mathbb{R}^{d})) for all \mu. To define parallel transport, we are interested in vector field along a curve, which we decided to be given by a Lagrangian formulation, hence we shall naturally be interested in Lagrangian vector field.